The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 26 September is 368,919 (655.4 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 22 September, there were 29,636 new confirmed cases (52.7 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 15 September, there were 18,600 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 59% (11036 extra cases).
